<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-1054] isSuper flag in cfstore is wrongly set in 0.7</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1054</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In 0.7, following &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16&quot; title=&quot;Memory efficient compactions &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-16&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-16&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the isSuper in ColumnFamilyStore is not set correctly (if I&apos;m correct). &lt;br/&gt;
This is because when the model is applied (AddColumnFamily.applyModels()) the columnFamilyStore&lt;br/&gt;
is created before the call to DataDescriptor.setTableDefinition. But the createColumnFamilyStore() &lt;br/&gt;
function retrieve the columnType. This thus always return a null that end up in a &quot;Super&quot;.equals(null)&lt;br/&gt;
that always sets the flag to false.&lt;br/&gt;
That being said, the isSuper flag of columnFamilyStore is never used. &lt;br/&gt;
I propose thus to get ride of this flag completely since if needed in the future, the column type can &lt;br/&gt;
always be retrieved from the table and cfname directly (the attached patch do just that).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
